sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM control_codes
WHERE status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
Active control codes refer to control codes that are currently in use or applicable; 
The version number represents the iteration or update of the control code, with higher version numbers indicating more recent updates; 
The 'created by' and 'updated by' refer to the users who originally created and last modified the control code, respectively.

sql:
SELECT version_number, description
FROM control_code_versions
WHERE code_id = 0 AND status = 'active';

SELECT name
FROM control_codes
ORDER BY name;

external_knowledge:
Recently resurfaced; refers to control codes that have been used within the last 30 days (last_used_at >= DATE('now', '-30 days')); 
Peak versions; refers to the maximum version number for each control code (MAX(cv.version_number));
Masterminds; refers to the users who created the last version of each control code (u.user_name);
Revived; refers to control codes that have been used after a period of not being used, implying a form of reuse or reactivation.
